   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Text Classification Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook handles the second stage of our pipeline: Character Classification.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Inputs\n",
    "- **`intermediate_boxes_expanded.json`**: This file contains the bounding box annotations output from `YOLO_training.ipynb`.\n",
    "- **Extended Datasets**: To make the classification more accurate, several other datasets were added, including:\n",
    "  - The `emnist` dataset.\n",
    "  - `/kaggle/input/datasets/mostafiz53/basicfinal` (available at [https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mostafiz53/basicfinal](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mostafiz53/basicfinal)).\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Important Configuration Note:** Several files that were generated during this script's execution were added back to this script as input in specific folders. To make this run properly in a new environment, **paths may need to be adjusted** to point to your local or Kaggle directories appropriately."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f5d345e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Dataset Ingestion\n",
    "\n",
    "Aggregate training data from three sources to build a diverse character classifier:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Source | Description |\n",
    "| :--- | :--- |\n",
    "| **Synthetic crops** (`classifier_dataset/`) | Character crops extracted during synthetic page generation (up to 1,500 per class). |\n",
    "| **CMATERdb** | Curated handwritten Bengali character dataset. |\n",
    "| **EMNIST** | Extended MNIST dataset covering handwritten English letters and digits. |\n",
    "\n",
    "Each source is ingested by its own function. Classes are mapped to the competition's target Unicode labels.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Path note:** `classifier_dataset/` must be available in the Kaggle input path. If running locally, adjust `CLASSIFIER_DIR` to point to the directory produced by the data-generation script."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "_cell_guid": "b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19",
    "_uuid": "8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5",
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-01T03:59:11.413387Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-01T03:59:11.412650Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-06-01T03:59:11.417603Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-06-01T03:59:11.416814Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2026-06-01T03:59:11.413354Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# --- PATH CONFIGURATION ---\n",
    "# ANNOTATIONS_DIR: Competition training annotations. Add the competition dataset\n",
    "#   ('handwritten-multiscript-character-segmentation-recognition') via Kaggle '+ Add Data'.\n",
    "# SYNTHETIC_INPUT_DIR: Output of kaggle_text_classifier_data_generation.py uploaded as a\n",
    "#   Kaggle notebook dataset. Update the slug to match your uploaded dataset.\n",
    "# CMATER_INPUT_DIR: The basicfinal dataset from https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mostafiz53/basicfinal\n",
    "#   Add it via Kaggle '+ Add Data'. The internal subdirectory path shown below may vary —\n",
    "#   verify the exact folder structure after adding.\n",
    "# MASTER_DATASET_DIR: Writable working directory where all crops are unified. No change needed on Kaggle.\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import shutil\n",
    "from torchvision import datasets\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "import random\n",
    "# --- 1. CONFIGURATION PATHS ---\n",
    "# The Kaggle hackathon target annotations\n",
    "ANNOTATIONS_DIR = \"/kaggle/input/competitions/handwritten-multiscript-character-segmentation-recognition/JU_CMATER/train/annotations\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# The master output folder we will feed to ResNet/EfficientNet\n",
    "MASTER_DATASET_DIR = \"/kaggle/working/classifier_dataset\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Update these to match your Kaggle 'input' panel paths!\n",
    "SYNTHETIC_INPUT_DIR = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/thenamelessmonster/comsys7-text-classification/classifier_dataset\" \n",
    "CMATER_INPUT_DIR = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/mostafiz53/basicfinal/BasicFinalDatabase/BasicFinalDatabase/Train\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e17b1c33",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 1a — Per-class Limits\n",
    "\n",
    "Cap the number of images taken from each source to prevent any single, large dataset from dominating the training distribution:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `MAX_SYNTHETIC_PER_CLASS = 1500` — synthetic crops (controlled variety, high volume)\n",
    "- `MAX_EXTERNAL_PER_CLASS = 1000` — CMATERdb / EMNIST (real handwriting, limited volume)\n",
    "\n",
    "After ingestion, all images land in a unified `classifier_dataset/` folder organised by Unicode hex class name."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "_cell_guid": "b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19",
    "_uuid": "8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5",
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-01T03:48:56.390317Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-01T03:48:56.389928Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-06-01T03:48:56.859011Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-06-01T03:48:56.858335Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2026-06-01T03:48:56.390293Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "1. Scanning JSONs for target classes and translating U+ codes...\n",
      "   -> Locked in exactly 135 target classes.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "MAX_SYNTHETIC_PER_CLASS = 1500\n",
    "MAX_EXTERNAL_PER_CLASS = 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 2. EXTRACT & TRANSLATE TARGET CLASSES ---\n",
    "print(\"1. Scanning JSONs for target classes and translating U+ codes...\")\n",
    "target_classes = set()\n",
    "\n",
    "# CRITICAL: We save this to disk for the final submission script!\n",
    "hackathon_label_map = {} \n",
    "\n",
    "for json_path in glob.glob(os.path.join(ANNOTATIONS_DIR, \"*.json\")):\n",
    "    with open(json_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n",
    "        data = json.load(f)\n",
    "        for shape in data.get('shapes', []):\n",
    "            label = shape.get('label')\n",
    "            if label:\n",
    "                try:\n",
    "                    # FIX: Convert the literal string \"U+0041\" into the actual character 'A'\n",
    "                    if label.startswith(\"U+\"):\n",
    "                        actual_char = chr(int(label.replace(\"U+\", \"\"), 16))\n",
    "                    else:\n",
    "                        actual_char = label\n",
    "                        \n",
    "                    # Get our universal Hex code\n",
    "                    char_hex = actual_char.encode('utf-8').hex()\n",
    "                    target_classes.add(char_hex)\n",
    "                    \n",
    "                    # Store the mapping (e.g., e0a695 -> \"U+0995\")\n",
    "                    hackathon_label_map[char_hex] = label \n",
    "                except Exception as e:\n",
    "                    pass\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"   -> Locked in exactly {len(target_classes)} target classes.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save the mapping file for the final submission\n",
    "with open('/kaggle/working/hackathon_label_map.json', 'w') as f:\n",
    "    json.dump(hackathon_label_map, f)\n",
    "\n",
    "for target_hex in target_classes:\n",
    "    os.makedirs(os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, target_hex), exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 3. INGEST SYNTHETIC CROPS ---\n",
    "def ingest_synthetic():\n",
    "    print(\"2. Ingesting Synthetic Data...\")\n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(SYNTHETIC_INPUT_DIR):\n",
    "        print(f\"   -> [WARNING] Synthetic input not found at {SYNTHETIC_INPUT_DIR}\")\n",
    "        return\n",
    "        \n",
    "    copied = 0\n",
    "    for target_hex in target_classes:\n",
    "        src_folder = os.path.join(SYNTHETIC_INPUT_DIR, target_hex)\n",
    "        dst_folder = os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, target_hex)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if os.path.exists(src_folder):\n",
    "            images = os.listdir(src_folder)[:MAX_SYNTHETIC_PER_CLASS]\n",
    "            for img in images:\n",
    "                shutil.copy(os.path.join(src_folder, img), os.path.join(dst_folder, img))\n",
    "                copied += 1\n",
    "    print(f\"   -> Successfully transferred {copied} synthetic crops.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 4. INGEST CMATERdb (Bengali) ---\n",
    "def ingest_cmaterdb():\n",
    "    print(\"3. Ingesting CMATERdb (Bengali)...\")\n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(CMATER_INPUT_DIR):\n",
    "        print(f\"   -> [WARNING] CMATERdb not found at {CMATER_INPUT_DIR}\")\n",
    "        return\n",
    "\n",
    "    BENGALI_ALPHABET = \"অআইঈউঊঋএঐওঔকখগঘঙচছজঝঞটঠডঢণতথদধনপফবভমযরলশষসহড়ঢ়য়ৎংঃঁ\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    copied = 0\n",
    "    for i, char in enumerate(BENGALI_ALPHABET):\n",
    "        folder_num = str(172 + i)\n",
    "        char_hex = char.encode('utf-8').hex()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if char_hex in target_classes:\n",
    "            src_folder = os.path.join(CMATER_INPUT_DIR, folder_num)\n",
    "            dst_folder = os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, char_hex)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if os.path.exists(src_folder):\n",
    "                images = os.listdir(src_folder)[:MAX_EXTERNAL_PER_CLASS]\n",
    "                for img in images:\n",
    "                    shutil.copy(os.path.join(src_folder, img), os.path.join(dst_folder, f\"cmater_{img}\"))\n",
    "                    copied += 1\n",
    "    print(f\"   -> Successfully transferred {copied} Bengali crops.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 5. INGEST EMNIST (English) VIA PYTORCH ---\n",
    "def ingest_emnist():\n",
    "    print(\"4. Downloading and Ingesting EMNIST via PyTorch...\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def get_emnist_char(label_int):\n",
    "        if 0 <= label_int <= 9:   return chr(label_int + 48)\n",
    "        if 10 <= label_int <= 35: return chr(label_int + 55)\n",
    "        if 36 <= label_int <= 61: return chr(label_int + 61)\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        emnist_data = datasets.EMNIST(root='/kaggle/working/data', split='byclass', train=True, download=True)\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"   -> [ERROR] PyTorch EMNIST download failed: {e}\")\n",
    "        return\n",
    "\n",
    "    class_counts = {k: 0 for k in target_classes}\n",
    "    copied = 0\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for img, label in emnist_data:\n",
    "        char_str = get_emnist_char(label)\n",
    "        if not char_str: continue\n",
    "            \n",
    "        char_hex = char_str.encode('utf-8').hex()\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if char_hex in target_classes and class_counts[char_hex] < MAX_EXTERNAL_PER_CLASS:\n",
    "            dst_folder = os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, char_hex)\n",
    "            img_name = f\"emnist_{label}_{class_counts[char_hex]}.jpg\"\n",
    "            img.save(os.path.join(dst_folder, img_name))\n",
    "            \n",
    "            class_counts[char_hex] += 1\n",
    "            copied += 1\n",
    "            \n",
    "            english_hexes = [h for h in target_classes if len(h) <= 4] \n",
    "            if all(class_counts[h] >= MAX_EXTERNAL_PER_CLASS for h in english_hexes):\n",
    "                break\n",
    "                \n",
    "    print(f\"   -> Successfully transferred {copied} EMNIST crops.\")\n",
    "    shutil.rmtree('/kaggle/working/data', ignore_errors=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# --- 6. THE SANITY CHECK REPORT ---\n",
    "def run_sanity_check():\n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*50)\n",
    "    print(\"🔍 DATASET SANITY CHECK & REPORT\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\"*50)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(MASTER_DATASET_DIR):\n",
    "        print(\"[FAIL] Master dataset directory does not exist.\")\n",
    "        return\n",
    "\n",
    "    folders = [f for f in os.listdir(MASTER_DATASET_DIR) if os.path.isdir(os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, f))]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    total_images = 0\n",
    "    src_counts = {'Synthetic': 0, 'CMATERdb': 0, 'EMNIST': 0}\n",
    "    empty_folders = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    for folder in folders:\n",
    "        folder_path = os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, folder)\n",
    "        images = os.listdir(folder_path)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if not images:\n",
    "            empty_folders.append(folder)\n",
    "            \n",
    "        total_images += len(images)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        for img in images:\n",
    "            if img.startswith('cmater_'):\n",
    "                src_counts['CMATERdb'] += 1\n",
    "            elif img.startswith('emnist_'):\n",
    "                src_counts['EMNIST'] += 1\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                src_counts['Synthetic'] += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Total Target Classes (Folders): {len(folders)} / {len(target_classes)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Total Images Harvested: {total_images:,}\\n\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"📊 Source Breakdown:\")\n",
    "    for src, count in src_counts.items():\n",
    "        percentage = (count / total_images * 100) if total_images > 0 else 0\n",
    "        print(f\"  - {src}: {count:,} images ({percentage:.1f}%)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if empty_folders:\n",
    "        print(f\"\\n⚠️ WARNING: Found {len(empty_folders)} empty folders! (Missing data for these characters)\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"\\n✅ SUCCESS: No empty folders detected. All classes have data.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"\\n🔬 Random 5-Class Sampling Matrix:\")\n",
    "    sample_folders = random.sample(folders, min(5, len(folders)))\n",
    "    for folder in sample_folders:\n",
    "        folder_path = os.path.join(MASTER_DATASET_DIR, folder)\n",
    "        images = os.listdir(folder_path)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Pull original Kaggle label from our dictionary mapping\n",
    "        kaggle_label = hackathon_label_map.get(folder, \"??\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        syn = sum(1 for i in images if not i.startswith(('cmater_', 'emnist_')))\n",
    "        cmat = sum(1 for i in images if i.startswith('cmater_'))\n",
    "        emn = sum(1 for i in images if i.startswith('emnist_'))\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(f\"  [{kaggle_label}] (Hex: {folder[:6]}...) -> Total: {len(images):4} | Syn: {syn:4} | CMATER: {cmat:4} | EMNIST: {emn:4}\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\"*50 + \"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
